                comment_content_json:
                  '{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Dear Dr. Peter Cowan, regarding the tendon, I thought it would be good to consider not only the effects of low-frequency electromagnetic fields alone; we could add that fluctuations in magnetic fields in windings and in the electrical network of substations can generate stationary or variable electric fields (Maxwell\'s Laws), and these, with a certain potential and electric charge, can act as discharges in humans and animals. If these discharges strike the head, they must reach the ground through the nearest point, in this case the tendon area, thus affecting its tissues, which would be dismembered."}]}]}',
