              thread_id: 77158,
              subcategory: null,
              comment_type: 'REVIEW',
              document_type: 'PREREGISTRATION',
              parent_comment: null,
              comment_content_json:
                '{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"General Assessment:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This study proposes a controlled experimental approach to a controversial and often under-researched topic: the biological impact of extremely low-frequency electromagnetic fields (ELF-EMF) on connective tissue. From a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"biotechnological and molecular biology perspective"},{"type":"text","text":", the use of a 2×2 factorial design combined with high-throughput multi-omics (RNA-seq and Luminex) is a robust way to move beyond epidemiological correlations toward mechanistic evidence. The project is well-structured, although it currently lacks a formal reference section to ground its theoretical premises."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Technical Commentary:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The primary strength of this proposal lies in the integration of transcriptomic and proteomic data to evaluate the extracellular matrix (ECM) and immune response. From a molecular biology standpoint, the focus on the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"MMP, ADAMTS, and TIMP families"},{"type":"text","text":" is highly appropriate, as these are the key effectors of matrix remodeling. However, I have a few technical observations:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Tissue Heterogeneity in Bulk RNA-seq:"},{"type":"text","text":" Since the authors are performing "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"whole-joint RNA sequencing"},{"type":"text","text":", the signal from specialized tissues (like the ACL or meniscus) might be diluted by more abundant tissues like bone or synovium. From a biotechnological data-analysis perspective, I suggest the authors consider using "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"deconvolution algorithms"},{"type":"text","text":" to estimate cell-type proportions or ensure that the homogenization process is highly standardized to maintain reproducibility across the $n=6$ samples."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Field Uniformity & Non-Thermal Effects:"},{"type":"text","text":" While the use of Helmholtz coils is a standard biotechnological approach for EMF studies, the \\"anti-Helmholtz\\" configuration for the sham group is crucial. I recommend that the authors explicitly monitor and report the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"vibration and acoustic profiles"},{"type":"text","text":" of the coils, as these can sometimes act as confounding mechanical stimuli in musculoskeletal studies."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Protein-Transcript Correlation:"},{"type":"text","text":" The use of Luminex for serum cytokines is an excellent secondary measure. However, the authors should be cautious when correlating systemic (serum) protein levels with local (joint) transcriptomic signatures, as the early inflammatory response (Day 3) might still be highly localized."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Absence of References:"},{"type":"text","text":" Critically, the proposal "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"lacks a reference section"},{"type":"text","text":". In a field like EMF research, which is prone to bias, it is essential to cite the specific studies that justify the 50 mG/60 Hz parameters and the previous correlations found between ELF-EMF and musculoskeletal integrity. Without this literature, the scientific rationale remains partially unsupported."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Conclusion:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The study is technically sound and addresses a relevant environmental health question with a modern molecular toolkit. The sample size ($n=6$) is adequate for a discovery-based pilot study. If the authors address the potential for signal dilution in bulk RNA-seq and provide the missing bibliographic support, this work will provide valuable mechanistic data on how non-thermal environmental factors modify tissue susceptibility to injury."}]}]}',
